/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-explorer-002.log:1451:/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/runtime/logs/codex-atlas-far-field-pressure-harmonic-loophole-strategy-001-strategizer.log:6533:execution/agents/library/factual/navier-stokes/vasseur-de-giorgi/post-2007-beta-landscape.md:45:**Tao (2016, JAMS) connection:** Shows that blowup can occur for "averaged NS" — proving that any regularity proof must use the *specific algebraic structure* of the NS nonlinearity. Generic methods like De Giorgi iteration (which use only energy-level properties + quadratic structure) cannot suffice for full regularity. This independently explains the 4/3 barrier from a different angle.
