/Users/seanross/kingdom_of_god/home-base/current_hunts/big-thinkers/research-systems/codex-atlas/execution/instances/concavity-survey/library-inbox/exploration-001-classical-eigenvalue-concavity.md:161:**From Tao's notes (Proposition 3):** The map A ↦ λ₁(A) + ... + λ_k(A) is **convex** on H_n; dually, A ↦ λ_{n-k+1}(A) + ... + λₙ(A) is **concave**. These are "the next best thing to linear" — minimax expressions.
